      "author": "Wanjin5508",
      "description": "## Vault Coach 1.0.0\r\n\r\nFirst stable release. Vault Coach is a local-first knowledge Q&A plugin for Obsidian, powered by Advanced RAG and a locally-running Ollama service. Your data never leaves your machine.\r\n\r\n### What's included\r\n\r\n**Retrieval**\r\n- Heading-aware chunking with paragraph aggregation and character-window fallback\r\n- TF-IDF keyword search with phrase and heading score bonuses\r\n- Semantic vector search via Ollama embeddings (L2-normalized cosine similarity)\r\n- Hybrid retrieval with Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF)\r\n- Query rewrite via local LLM before retrieval\r\n- Rerank: external `/v1/rerank` service or local heuristic fallback\r\n\r\n**Memory & Persistence**\r\n- Long-term memory: LLM-extracted facts injected across sessions, with recency-weighted LRU eviction\r\n- Conversation persistence: chat history restored on restart\r\n- Incremental index sync: debounce + file-threshold dual strategy on vault file changes\r\n- Knowledge base snapshot: full index persisted to disk and restored on startup\r\n\r\n**Generation**\r\n- True streaming output via `fetch` + `ReadableStream` (Electron/Desktop)\r\n- Markdown-rendered answers via Obsidian's `MarkdownRenderer`\r\n- Collapsible source display with click-to-navigate\r\n\r\n**Interface**\r\n- Right sidebar `ItemView` with retrieval mode switcher (keyword / vector / hybrid)\r\n- Full settings UI covering all RAG, model, memory, and sync parameters\r\n\r\n### Requirements\r\n- Obsidian 1.5.0+\r\n- Ollama running locally with at least one chat model and one embedding model",
